# FreshLens — API & ML

Applies when editing `apps/api/` or `packages/ml/`.

## API (FastAPI)

- Async endpoints; shared Python ecosystem with ML worker
- Protected routes: validate Supabase JWT, set `app.tenant_id` on DB session
- Scan upload flow:

```python
# ✅ Correct — enqueue and return immediately
@router.post("/scan", status_code=202)
async def create_scan(...):
    image_path = await store_image(file)
    scan_id = await create_pending_scan(tenant_id, image_path)
    process_scan.delay(scan_id)  # Celery
    return {"scan_id": scan_id, "status": "processing"}

# ❌ Wrong — never inline inference
# result = model.predict(image)  # in request handler
```

## ML worker (Celery)

- Lives in `packages/ml/`; consumes queue; writes to Postgres
- Store `model_version` on each scan result
- Training artifacts: MobileNetV3 or ResNet50 on Fruits-360 + Kaggle freshness data

## Redis

All keys prefixed: `tenant:{tenant_id}:queue:...`, `tenant:{tenant_id}:cache:...`
